HEADWORD: Pseudo-hyperthophic
<hw>Pseu`do-hy`per*thoph"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Pseudo-</ets> + <ets>hypertrophic</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Falsely hypertrophic; <as>as,
<ex>pseudo-hypertrophic</ex> paralysis, a variety of paralysis in which
the muscles are apparently enlarged, but are really degenerated and
replaced by fat</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pseudologist</ent>⟦br⟧
